fields.bio:
Born in South Africa, Kasiddy specialises in underwater photography. She grew up with a fascination for the ocean and is a self confessed water baby, living as much in the water as possible than out of it. 

Her latest exhibition in London sold out solidifying her trajectory as one of the most popular underwater photographers currently out there.

Jessie Jackson is a digital artist born in the sleepy town of gävling on the west coast of Sweden. 
Inspired by her love of nature and all things abstract her popularity has grown with every exhibition.

Annie's love for photography was so great that she changed her surname to Lebofitz, as a homage to her favourite photographer Annie Lebowitz.
Her passion and work ethic has made her one of Swedens most sought after commercial photographers, however it is her personal work in her exhibits that draw the most attention. Risky and over the top, they are not only gaining in popularity but in price too as they are becoming sought after throughout not only Sweden but the world.

fields.title: New artist focus: Kasiddy Obzitz
fields.content:
What inspired you to become an underwater photographer?

Underwater photography is a unique and challenging field. What sparked your interest, and how did you decide to pursue a career capturing the beauty beneath the waves?
Can you share a memorable experience or encounter you've had while capturing images underwater?
Every dive must bring its own set of challenges and surprises. Tell us about a particularly memorable moment or an encounter that left a lasting impact on you during one of your underwater photography expeditions.

What kind of equipment and techniques do you use to capture stunning underwater images?
Underwater photography requires specialized gear and techniques. Could you walk us through the equipment you use and any unique approaches you've developed to overcome the technical challenges of shooting in an underwater environment?

How do you navigate the delicate balance between capturing the beauty of marine life and respecting the underwater ecosystem?

With concerns about environmental impact and conservation, how do you ensure that your work as an underwater photographer aligns with sustainable practices? How can underwater photographers contribute to the preservation of marine life and habitats?

What advice do you have for aspiring underwater photographers looking to enter the field?

For those who are inspired by your work and want to pursue a career in underwater photography, what advice do you have? Are there specific skills, knowledge, or experiences that aspiring underwater photographers should focus on to thrive in this challenging and rewarding profession?

fields.title: Artists View: Jessie Jackson on AI
fields.content:
Q: How do you view the role of artificial intelligence (AI) in enhancing artistic expression?

A: AI, in my opinion, serves as a valuable tool that augments creativity rather than replacing the human touch. It helps artists overcome creative blocks, offering new possibilities and pushing the boundaries of traditional artistic methods.

Q: What challenges and ethical considerations do you see arising with the integration of AI into the creative process?

A: There are valid concerns, especially regarding issues of authorship, plagiarism, and authenticity. It's crucial for artists to maintain control over their work and establish clear ethical guidelines within the art community as AI-generated art gains popularity.

Q: How has the creative process in digital art been transformed by the integration of AI tools?

A: AI has become a collaborative partner, suggesting ideas and perspectives that I might not have considered. It allows for efficient experimentation with different styles and techniques, leading to a continuous refinement and evolution of the artistic work.

Q: Can you elaborate on AI's role as a muse in the creative process?

A: Absolutely. AI-generated art serves as a muse by inspiring new ideas and pushing artists to explore uncharted territories. Its ability to analyze vast datasets and generate unique patterns acts as a catalyst for artists seeking fresh perspectives.

Q: Looking ahead, how do you envision the future relationship between AI and art?

A: I see a future where AI and art coexist harmoniously. It's important to recognize that AI is a tool, not a replacement for human creativity. Artists have the responsibility to harness its potential while shaping the evolving relationship between AI and art.
